{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":432,"text":"Now, I don't usually like cartoons,"},{"time":3154,"text":"I don't think many of them are funny,"},{"time":5664,"text":"I find them weird. But I love this cartoon from the New Yorker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10887,"text":"(Text: Never, ever think outside the box.) (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13499,"text":"So, the guy is telling the cat,"},{"time":15968,"text":"don't you dare think outside the box."},{"time":21339,"text":"Well, I'm afraid I used to be the cat."},{"time":24646,"text":"I always wanted to be outside the box."},{"time":27704,"text":"And it's partly because I came to this field"},{"time":31186,"text":"from a different background, chemist and a bacterial geneticist."},{"time":36399,"text":"So, what people were saying to me"},{"time":39001,"text":"about the cause of cancer, sources of cancer,"},{"time":42192,"text":"or, for that matter, why you are who you are,"},{"time":45273,"text":"didn't make sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47147,"text":"So, let me quickly try and tell you why I thought that"},{"time":50194,"text":"and how I went about it."},{"time":52795,"text":"So, to begin with, however,"},{"time":55227,"text":"I have to give you a very, very quick lesson"},{"time":59653,"text":"in developmental biology,"},{"time":61420,"text":"with apologies to those of you who know some biology."},{"time":65482,"text":"So, when your mom and dad met,"},{"time":68496,"text":"there is a fertilized egg,"},{"time":71170,"text":"that round thing with that little blip."},{"time":73291,"text":"It grows and then it grows,"},{"time":76346,"text":"and then it makes this handsome man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80499,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":81914,"text":"So, this guy, with all the cells in his body,"},{"time":87572,"text":"all have the same genetic information."},{"time":91784,"text":"So how did his nose become his nose, his elbow his elbow,"},{"time":96159,"text":"and why doesn't he get up one morning"},{"time":98335,"text":"and have his nose turn into his foot?"},{"time":100895,"text":"It could. It has the genetic information."},{"time":104135,"text":"You all remember, dolly,"},{"time":105343,"text":"it came from a single mammary cell."},{"time":108024,"text":"So, why doesn't it do it?"},{"time":109958,"text":"So, have a guess of how many cells he has in his body."},{"time":115461,"text":"Somewhere between 10 trillion to 70 trillion cells in his body."},{"time":122863,"text":"Trillion!"},{"time":124503,"text":"Now, how did these cells, all with the same genetic material,"},{"time":129141,"text":"make all those tissues?"},{"time":131349,"text":"And so, the question I raised before"},{"time":134493,"text":"becomes even more interesting if you thought about"},{"time":138107,"text":"the enormity of this in every one of your bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142693,"text":"Now, the dominant cancer theory would say"},{"time":145693,"text":"that there is a single oncogene"},{"time":148005,"text":"in a single cancer cell, and it would make you"},{"time":151709,"text":"a cancer victim."},{"time":154358,"text":"Well, this did not make sense to me."},{"time":158024,"text":"Do you even know how a trillion looks?"},{"time":161206,"text":"Now, let's look at it."},{"time":162925,"text":"There it comes, these zeroes after zeroes after zeroes."},{"time":167966,"text":"Now, if .0001 of these cells got mutated,"},{"time":174784,"text":"and .00001 got cancer, you will be a lump of cancer."},{"time":180041,"text":"You will have cancer all over you. And you're not."},{"time":182337,"text":"Why not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":184646,"text":"So, I decided over the years,"},{"time":188368,"text":"because of a series of experiments"},{"time":190296,"text":"that this is because of context and architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195176,"text":"And let me quickly tell you"},{"time":197353,"text":"some crucial experiment that was able to actually show this."},{"time":201280,"text":"To begin with, I came to work with this virus"},{"time":205191,"text":"that causes that ugly tumor in the chicken."},{"time":208584,"text":"Rous discovered this in 1911."},{"time":211944,"text":"It was the first cancer virus discovered,"},{"time":215509,"text":"and when I call it \"oncogene,\" meaning \"cancer gene.\""},{"time":220400,"text":"So, he made a filtrate, he took this filter"},{"time":223312,"text":"which was the liquid after he passed the tumor through a filter,"},{"time":227568,"text":"and he injected it to another chicken, and he got another tumor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231569,"text":"So, scientists were very excited,"},{"time":234280,"text":"and they said, a single oncogene can do it."},{"time":236448,"text":"All you need is a single oncogene."},{"time":238744,"text":"So, they put the cells in cultures, chicken cells,"},{"time":241639,"text":"dumped the virus on it,"},{"time":243674,"text":"and it would pile up,"},{"time":245123,"text":"and they would say, this is malignant and this is normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248144,"text":"And again this didn't make sense to me."},{"time":250162,"text":"So for various reasons, we took this oncogene,"},{"time":253448,"text":"attached it to a blue marker,"},{"time":255760,"text":"and we injected it into the embryos."},{"time":258768,"text":"Now look at that. There is that beautiful feather in the embryo."},{"time":262961,"text":"Every one of those blue cells are a cancer gene"},{"time":267240,"text":"inside a cancer cell, and they're part of the feather."},{"time":271656,"text":"So, when we dissociated the feather and put it in a dish,"},{"time":276256,"text":"we got a mass of blue cells."},{"time":278968,"text":"So, in the chicken you get a tumor,"},{"time":280434,"text":"in the embryo you don't,"},{"time":282138,"text":"you dissociate, you put it in a dish, you get another tumor."},{"time":286130,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":287353,"text":"That means that microenvironment"},{"time":290337,"text":"and the context which surrounds those cells"},{"time":294346,"text":"actually are telling the cancer gene and the cancer cell what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301273,"text":"Now, let's take a normal example."},{"time":304585,"text":"The normal example, let's take the human mammary gland."},{"time":307770,"text":"I work on breast cancer."},{"time":309250,"text":"So, here is a lovely human breast."},{"time":312257,"text":"And many of you know how it looks,"},{"time":314205,"text":"except that inside that breast, there are all these"},{"time":317058,"text":"pretty, developing, tree-like structures."},{"time":320435,"text":"So, we decided that what we like to do"},{"time":323333,"text":"is take just a bit of that mammary gland,"},{"time":326293,"text":"which is called an \"acinus,\""},{"time":328325,"text":"where there are all these little things inside the breast"},{"time":331966,"text":"where the milk goes, and the end of the nipple"},{"time":335509,"text":"comes through that little tube when the baby sucks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339053,"text":"And we said, wonderful! Look at this pretty structure."},{"time":342460,"text":"We want to make this a structure, and ask the question,"},{"time":346229,"text":"how do the cells do that?"},{"time":347933,"text":"So, we took the red cells --"},{"time":349725,"text":"you see the red cells are surrounded by blue,"},{"time":352973,"text":"other cells that squeeze them, and behind it"},{"time":356302,"text":"is material that people thought was mainly inert,"},{"time":360020,"text":"and it was just having a structure to keep the shape,"},{"time":363617,"text":"and so we first photographed it"},{"time":366545,"text":"with the electron microscope years and years ago,"},{"time":369313,"text":"and you see this cell is actually quite pretty."},{"time":372369,"text":"It has a bottom, it has a top,"},{"time":374832,"text":"it is secreting gobs and gobs of milk,"},{"time":377513,"text":"because it just came from an early pregnant mouse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380705,"text":"You take these cells, you put them in a dish,"},{"time":383032,"text":"and within three days, they look like that."},{"time":386377,"text":"They completely forget."},{"time":389537,"text":"So you take them out, you put them in a dish,"},{"time":392337,"text":"they don't make milk. They completely forget."},{"time":395000,"text":"For example, here is a lovely yellow droplet of milk"},{"time":399899,"text":"on the left, there is nothing on the right."},{"time":402154,"text":"Look at the nuclei. The nuclei in the cell on the left"},{"time":405883,"text":"is in the animal, the one on the right is in a dish."},{"time":409379,"text":"They are completely different from each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412115,"text":"So, what does this tell you?"},{"time":414140,"text":"This tells you that here also, context overrides."},{"time":419107,"text":"In different contexts, cells do different things."},{"time":422492,"text":"But how does context signal?"},{"time":425237,"text":"So, Einstein said that"},{"time":427779,"text":"\"For an idea that does not first seem insane, there is no hope.\""},{"time":434432,"text":"So, you can imagine the amount of skepticism"},{"time":440392,"text":"I received -- couldn't get money,"},{"time":442793,"text":"couldn't do a whole lot of other things,"},{"time":444736,"text":"but I'm so glad it all worked out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446465,"text":"So, we made a section of the mammary gland of the mouse,"},{"time":450280,"text":"and all those lovely acini are there,"},{"time":453463,"text":"every one of those with the red around them are an acinus,"},{"time":457674,"text":"and we said okay, we are going to try and make this,"},{"time":461368,"text":"and I said, maybe that red stuff"},{"time":464600,"text":"around the acinus that people think there's just a structural scaffold,"},{"time":469725,"text":"maybe it has information,"},{"time":471665,"text":"maybe it tells the cells what to do, maybe it tells the nucleus what to do."},{"time":476231,"text":"So I said, extracellular matrix, which is this stuff"},{"time":480514,"text":"called ECM, signals and actually tells the cells what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484905,"text":"So, we decided to make things that would look like that."},{"time":488672,"text":"We found some gooey material"},{"time":491552,"text":"that had the right extracellular matrix in it,"},{"time":494427,"text":"we put the cells in it, and lo and behold,"},{"time":496966,"text":"in about four days, they got reorganized"},{"time":499787,"text":"and on the right, is what we can make in culture."},{"time":503195,"text":"On the left is what's inside the animal, we call it in vivo,"},{"time":507691,"text":"and the one in culture was full of milk,"},{"time":510275,"text":"the lovely red there is full of milk."},{"time":513075,"text":"So, we Got Milk, for the American audience."},{"time":516491,"text":"All right. And here is this beautiful human cell,"},{"time":521835,"text":"and you can imagine that here also, context goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526781,"text":"So, what do we do now?"},{"time":529497,"text":"I made a radical hypothesis."},{"time":531721,"text":"I said, if it's true that architecture is dominant,"},{"time":538384,"text":"architecture restored to a cancer cell"},{"time":542870,"text":"should make the cancer cell think it's normal."},{"time":545859,"text":"Could this be done?"},{"time":547343,"text":"So, we tried it."},{"time":549871,"text":"In order to do that, however,"},{"time":551909,"text":"we needed to have a method of distinguishing normal from malignant,"},{"time":556794,"text":"and on the left is the single normal cell,"},{"time":560791,"text":"human breast, put in three-dimensional gooey gel"},{"time":564754,"text":"that has extracellular matrix, it makes all these beautiful structures."},{"time":568618,"text":"On the right, you see it looks very ugly,"},{"time":571506,"text":"the cells continue to grow,"},{"time":573154,"text":"the normal ones stop."},{"time":574730,"text":"And you see here in higher magnification"},{"time":577562,"text":"the normal acinus and the ugly tumor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581914,"text":"So we said, what is on the surface of these ugly tumors?"},{"time":586138,"text":"Could we calm them down --"},{"time":588306,"text":"they were signaling like crazy and they have pathways all messed up --"},{"time":593226,"text":"and make them to the level of the normal?"},{"time":596290,"text":"Well, it was wonderful. Boggles my mind."},{"time":601010,"text":"This is what we got."},{"time":603171,"text":"We can revert the malignant phenotype."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606850,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":609418,"text":"And in order to show you that the malignant phenotype"},{"time":612530,"text":"I didn't just choose one,"},{"time":614248,"text":"here are little movies, sort of fuzzy,"},{"time":617018,"text":"but you see that on the left are the malignant cells,"},{"time":620674,"text":"all of them are malignant,"},{"time":622018,"text":"we add one single inhibitor in the beginning,"},{"time":626818,"text":"and look what happens, they all look like that."},{"time":630275,"text":"We inject them into the mouse, the ones on the right,"},{"time":633722,"text":"and none of them would make tumors."},{"time":635962,"text":"We inject the other ones in the mouse, 100 percent tumors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639498,"text":"So, it's a new way of thinking about cancer,"},{"time":642170,"text":"it's a hopeful way of thinking about cancer."},{"time":644570,"text":"We should be able to be dealing with these things at this level,"},{"time":648546,"text":"and these conclusions say that growth and malignant behavior"},{"time":654458,"text":"is regulated at the level of tissue organization"},{"time":658330,"text":"and that the tissue organization is dependent"},{"time":662322,"text":"on the extracellular matrix and the microenvironment."},{"time":666018,"text":"All right, thus form and function interact dynamically and reciprocally."},{"time":673649,"text":"And here is another five seconds of repose,"},{"time":677769,"text":"is my mantra. Form and function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682191,"text":"And of course, we now ask, where do we go now?"},{"time":685837,"text":"We'd like to take this kind of thinking into the clinic."},{"time":688832,"text":"But before we do that, I'd like you to think"},{"time":692756,"text":"that at any given time when you're sitting there,"},{"time":696344,"text":"in your 70 trillion cells,"},{"time":699357,"text":"the extracellular matrix signaling to your nucleus,"},{"time":702830,"text":"the nucleus is signaling to your extracellular matrix"},{"time":705908,"text":"and this is how your balance is kept and restored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711902,"text":"We have made a lot of discoveries,"},{"time":714117,"text":"we have shown that extracellular matrix talks to chromatin."},{"time":717205,"text":"We have shown that there's little pieces of DNA"},{"time":720652,"text":"on the specific genes of the mammary gland"},{"time":724475,"text":"that actually respond to extracellular matrix."},{"time":727339,"text":"It has taken many years, but it has been very rewarding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731036,"text":"And before I get to the next slide, I have to tell you"},{"time":735427,"text":"that there are so many additional discoveries to be made."},{"time":740539,"text":"There is so much mystery we don't know."},{"time":743067,"text":"And I always say to the students and post-docs I lecture to,"},{"time":747428,"text":"don't be arrogant, because arrogance kills curiosity."},{"time":753091,"text":"Curiosity and passion."},{"time":755283,"text":"You need to always think, what else needs to be discovered?"},{"time":759180,"text":"And maybe my discovery needs to be added to"},{"time":762155,"text":"or maybe it needs to be changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763947,"text":"So, we have now made an amazing discovery,"},{"time":767451,"text":"a post-doc in the lab who is a physicist asked me,"},{"time":770555,"text":"what do the cells do when you put them in?"},{"time":772732,"text":"What do they do in the beginning when they do?"},{"time":776026,"text":"I said, I don't know, we couldn't look at them."},{"time":777507,"text":"We didn't have high images in the old days."},{"time":780100,"text":"So she, being an imager and a physicist,"},{"time":782795,"text":"did this incredible thing."},{"time":784539,"text":"This is a single human breast cell in three dimensions."},{"time":788915,"text":"Look at it. It's constantly doing this."},{"time":791443,"text":"Has a coherent movement."},{"time":793539,"text":"You put the cancer cells there, and they do go all over,"},{"time":797873,"text":"they do this. They don't do this."},{"time":799777,"text":"And when we revert the cancer cell, it again does this."},{"time":803785,"text":"Absolutely boggles my mind."},{"time":805969,"text":"So the cell acts like an embryo. What an exciting thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811313,"text":"So I'd like to finish with a poem."},{"time":814169,"text":"Well I used to love English literature,"},{"time":817233,"text":"and I debated in college, which one should I do?"},{"time":819840,"text":"And unfortunately or fortunately, chemistry won."},{"time":824452,"text":"But here is a poem from Yeats. I'll just read you the last two lines."},{"time":830176,"text":"It's called \"Among the School Children.\""},{"time":832835,"text":"\"O body swayed to music / O brightening glance /"},{"time":837356,"text":"How [can we know] the dancer from the dance?\""},{"time":840506,"text":"And here is Merce Cunningham,"},{"time":842417,"text":"I was fortunate to dance with him when I was younger,"},{"time":845401,"text":"and here he is a dancer,"},{"time":847594,"text":"and while he is dancing, he is both the dancer and the dance."},{"time":850898,"text":"The minute he stops, we have neither."},{"time":854599,"text":"So it's like form and function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858073,"text":"Now, I'd like to show you a current picture of my group."},{"time":863852,"text":"I have been fortunate to have had these magnificant"},{"time":867380,"text":"students and post-docs who have taught me so much,"},{"time":870604,"text":"and I have had many of these groups come and go."},{"time":873867,"text":"They are the future and I try to make them not be afraid"},{"time":878444,"text":"of being the cat and being told,"},{"time":882147,"text":"don't think outside the box."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883740,"text":"And I'd like to leave you with this thought."},{"time":886235,"text":"On the left is water coming through the shore,"},{"time":890980,"text":"taken from a NASA satellite."},{"time":892875,"text":"On the right, there is a coral."},{"time":895924,"text":"Now if you take the mammary gland and spread it"},{"time":899926,"text":"and take the fat away, on a dish it looks like that."},{"time":903371,"text":"Do they look the same? Do they have the same patterns?"},{"time":906723,"text":"Why is it that nature keeps doing that over and over again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910675,"text":"And I'd like to submit to you"},{"time":913035,"text":"that we have sequenced the human genome,"},{"time":915212,"text":"we know everything about the sequence of the gene,"},{"time":918092,"text":"the language of the gene, the alphabet of the gene,"},{"time":920523,"text":"But we know nothing, but nothing,"},{"time":923762,"text":"about the language and alphabet of form."},{"time":928425,"text":"So, it's a wonderful new horizon,"},{"time":931469,"text":"it's a wonderful thing to discover for the young"},{"time":935219,"text":"and the passionate old, and that's me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937699,"text":"So go to it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":939747,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}